    <div class="body">
      My head canon for black holes is that there's an opposite anti-mass universe where time travels backwards (from our point of view) and black holes are spewing mass &amp; light into that universe until eventually everything collapses into a big crunch (which sets off our big bang, or the next universe).<br /><br />Feel it's got to be something neat and tidy (in terms of balancing out conservation of energy)
      
